news.title: Puravankara appoints Deepak Rastogi as Group CFO
news.para: Neeraj Gautam, who has been serving as the president-finance at Puravankara, has been elevated to the post of deputy chief financial officer.

news.title: UK construction growth slows to six-month low: Survey
news.para: The S&P Global Purchasing Managers' Index for the construction sector dropped to 53.3 in December from November's 55.2, its lowest since June and below all forecasts in a Reuters poll of economists.

news.title: House prices in UK drop by 0.2% in December 2024: Halifax
news.para: Halifax, part of Lloyds Banking Group, Britain's biggest mortgage lender, said house prices fell 0.2% in December after a 1.2% rise in November, and were 3.3% higher on the year - lower than the 4.2% rise forecast in a Reuters poll of economists.

news.title: Trichy: Police booked five people for illegal sand mining
news.para: The Srirangam police confiscated one unit of sand from a mini truck at a vacant plot in Tagore Street service road on Trichy – Chennai national highway near Srirangam.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto drop 18.7% in December 2024
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales fell 18.7% in December from November to 5,359 units, marking the lowest sales level since July, Toronto Regional Real Estate Board data showed. Compared to December 2023, sales were down 6.8%.

news.title: Number of foreclosed homes in China rose in 2024 amid property slump
news.para: The number of repossessed homes up for auction stood at 370,000 in 2024, up from 364,000 in 2023, the report from China Index Academy, an independent real estate research firm, said.

news.title: Housing sales up 7% at over 3.5 lakh units across eight cities in 2024: Knight Frank
news.para: Last month, real estate consultant Anarock, however, had reported that housing sales declined 4 per cent in 2024 to nearly 4.6 lakh units across seven major cities.

news.title: SC pulls up Maharashtra bodies for not paying villagers after acquiring lands
news.para: A bench of Justices Surya Kant and N Kotiswar Singh was hearing the case over the land acquired from the villagers of Jambhalkhori Borphadi in Beed district of Maharashtra for construction of a water tank under the Employees Guarantee Scheme in 2005.

news.title: Mumbai civic body revokes construction work ban in Byculla and Borivali
news.para: The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation, however, warned of imposing restrictions if construction projects are found contributing to air pollution.

news.title: Rajasthan government to introduce private land aggregation bill in assembly
news.para: As per the proposed bill, landowners will be provided with developed land instead of cash compensation as usual. A minimum of 25% developed land must be granted in exchange for compensation, according to the draft.

news.title: Delhi's groundwater extraction declined from 127% in 2013 to 99% in 2023: CGWA tells NGT
news.para: Earlier, the National Green Tribunal (NGT) had taken suo motu cognisance of a PTI report regarding a UN study predicting that several parts of the country could experience critically low groundwater availability by 2025.

news.title: Hong Kong struggles to improve conditions in tiny, crowded homes
news.para: More than 200,000 people in Hong Kong live in sub-divided flats like hers, often cloaked in a musty odour and plagued by bedbugs during sweltering summers.

news.title: Survey for land acquisition for Coimbatore metro project to begin soon
news.para: CMRL plans to establish its project office within the corporation office campus. Officials are also considering a suitable location on Dr Nanjappa Road.

news.title: Property owners receive compensation cheques affected by Hyderabad's metro phase II expansion
news.para: The seven and a half kilometre Old City Metro is expected to be completed in four years with an estimated cost of 2,741 crore. In total, a compensation of about 1,000 crore will be paid for a total of 1,100 properties.

news.title: New policy to distribute plots to farmers soon: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: In the 45-minute meeting, representatives from Bhartiya Kisan Parishad, All India Kisan Sabha, and Kisan Ekta Sangh highlighted key concerns over implementation of the 2013 Land Acquisition Act and allocation of 10% developed plots.

news.title: Four held for tampering with records of plots along Mumbai coastline
news.para: The accused were arrested last week by a special investigation team (SIT), which was set up following the Bombay High Court's order to probe the land scam, the official said.

news.title: Nashik civic body’s revenue drops by 16% in April-December of FY 2024-25
news.para: The civic body has collected around Rs 1,600 crore revenue through various taxes in the first nine months, against its projection of Rs 1,906 crore.

news.title: Mohali development body takes action against illegal construction in New Chandigarh
news.para: Notably, the notices were posted on structures that were already more than halfway built. The GMADA had earlier turned a blind eye when the foundations for these buildings were being dug.

news.title: Spyre VC invests Rs 3.5 crore in Spintly
news.para: Spintly plans to accelerate its market reach, increase its presence in different countries, strengthen senior management functions, and expand the scope of its smart building solutions.

news.title: Bring 1.35 crore khata-less properties into tax net: Karnataka CM
news.para: During a review meeting on the revenue performance of the stamps and registration department, the CM emphasised the importance of sanitizing the property registration records based on fake documents.
